  hotspots:
  - title: Walkway Toward the Torii
    body: "As you walk toward the torii, you are experiencing one of the most important
      ideas in Japanese garden design: miegakure, or \u201Chide and reveal.\u201D
      Rohoen was intentionally designed so that the entire garden is never visible
      at once; instead, curved paths slowly uncover new views as you move through
      the space. The torii adds another layer of meaning, since torii traditionally
      mark a transition from ordinary space into a more sacred or reflective one
      in Japanese culture."
    yaw: 0
    pitch: 0
    icon: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 7d2865e2b884e1a46be7144719039f15, type: 2}
